  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This method accounts for the compositional nature of the data-in which abundances reflect relative instead of absolute quantities-by assuming that the amount of correlations in a dataset is sparse.",
    "We ran FastSpar on the non-redundant set of predicted plasmids and ran it separately on the non-redundant set of reference plasmids.",
    "We performed a more careful analysis of plasmid pDOJH10S and its cognate host B. longum DJO10A by performing a read recruitment of metagenomes to both sequences together, using Bowtie 2 and allowing every read to align at most once (Supplementary Fig. 7f and Supplementary Table 13).",
    "Following Utter et al.",
    "91, we applied a detection threshold of >50% to identify the presence of the plasmid or host: 365 metagenomes contained the plasmid, 818 metagenomes contained the cognate host and 336 metagenomes contained both genomes (Jaccard index = 0.40)."
  ],
